msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Medical treatise in 50 chapters, 35 concerning reproduction and the final 15 addressing the soul and intellect from a neoplatonic perspective. Some marginal notes. Persian inscriptions recording births in A.H. 1236, 1243, and 1245 on the last page (f. 84v), suggesting use of the manuscript by a medical practitioner.

author.persName: Saʻīd ibn Hibat Allāh ibn al-Ḥusayn, 1004-1101
سعيد بن هبة الله بن الحسين

respStmt.persName: ʻAbd al-Raḥmān ibn ʻAbd al-Salām al-Ṣafūrī
عبد الرحمن بن عبد السلام الصفوري,

supportDesc.extent: 84 leaves : 255 x 172 (185 x 125-130) mm. bound to 257 x 182 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (modern) + 84 + i (modern); [1-84], modern foliation in pencil, upper left recto (f. 1-44 also foliated with eastern Arabic numerals in ink, upper left recto). Catchwords on each leaf, lower left verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in rapid naskh in black ink; pointed.

binding.p: Later morocco with gilt-stamped onlays of a central mandorla, two pendants on the vertical axis and cornerpieces.

origin.p: Copy completed in Mamluk Syria or Iraq by ʻAbd al-Raḥmān ibn ʻAbd al-Salām al-Ṣafūrī on 15 Jumādá al-Ākhirah A.H. 689 (colophon, f. 84r).

history.provenance: Several notes and ownership seals on first and last pages (f. 1r, 84v).
Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, Dec. 2000.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2012.
